        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=34200&TOPIC_ID=4575&FORUM_ID=11&CAT_ID=5&Forum_Title=Newbie+Hall&Topic_Title=Pierce+or+Bash%3F&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">That's right - don't listen to those wimps who don't melee after level 10.  Sure, you can't take a huge beating at higher levels, but there are still some situations where melee skills can be useful.  You can't always Fear your enemies away, Root doesn't always hold, and when your pet's at 2% and the enemy's at 10% you'd better step up and take a few hits.</P><P>The trick is to keep your weapons skills at a useable level (try to max them all), max out your Offense and Defense (and the only way to do that is in melee), dress for AC and HP, and use your spells.</P><P>Here's what I was doing at 30:  Sit the pet down where I'm pulling to.  Prep with Major Shielding, Spirit Armor, Grim Aura, Banshee Aura, Vampiric Embrace, med up a bit if necessary.  Pull with Vampiric Curse, run back to the pet.  Melee it down with the pet beating on it.  Toss in a Darkness to keep it from running.  If at half health (it happened occasionally), hit it with Spirit Tap.  Kill, rinse, repeat.</P><P>With Vampiric Curse covering early damage and procing a 42 point lifetap several times a battle (you <i>did</i> put starting points into Dex, didn't you? Heh heh...) it's not as bad as it sounds.  Weapon procs and the 12 point damage shield just add to the fun.</P><P>For doing things like that, piercing weapons are generally better due to the low delay.  There are some nice ones available at many levels.  1-hand blunt is slower, but getting one with a decent proc is probably easier.  2-hand blunt is just for practice, but there are some really nice ones at higher levels.</P><P><b>Morty Undercrypt</b>, Keeper of the <font color=red>NecroGnomicon</font id=red><BR><small>"Why am I still killing goblins?"</small><BR>E'ci<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
