        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Right, ok now wait until lvl 34 or 35 and go kill specs, dorfs, or halv (gnome guard) you will be dead in seconds if you try and do this.  Darkness pull, send pet, fear, DoTs (DoT and fear can change order), put CoB up, sit down and when mob gets low use the DoT life tap spell.<BR>Just to let you know, guard halv doubles for 90's, specs attack slow but hit for 80's, dorfs hit for 80's and pretty fast.  Stuff in OT hits for around double 70's, Giants (which when soloed give decent exp and amazing loot) hit for 80-90's.  Basically only step in when pet and mob are both really low and you don't want pet to die.</P><P>Oh i almost forgot velius mobs...wurms, well if you are meleeing the wurm then you are screwed, cougars 60's, walrus guys 60's again...oh and a LOT of velious mobs cast.</P><P>Only reason i really care to have my melee up is for when i'm in a low lvl zone with no pet and some stupid thing in there attacks me.</P><P><marquee><b><font=red> ABILLISTER "MONKEY" ABU-Povar</font></b></marquee><BR><marquee><a href="<a href="http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp" target="_blank">http://whiteangels.guildsofeq.com/MainFrame.asp</a>" target="_New">Sojourn's Talon</a></marquee><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
